a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:658:\"<p>Looking to migrate from Blogger to WordPress? Blogger is a good entry point for beginners to get started with blogging. Since Blogger.com is a free platform, many users choose it as their blogging platform when starting out. But it&#8217;s definitely not where you want to stay if you&#8217;re truly serious about blogging. Now that you&#8217;ve [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/move-from-blogger-to-wordpress-resolved/\">The 2019’s Guide to Moving a Blog From Blogger to WordPress (Resolved)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com\">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"Editorial Team\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25907:\"<p>Looking to migrate from Blogger to WordPress? Blogger is a good entry point for beginners to get started with blogging. Since Blogger.com is a free platform, many users choose it as their blogging platform when starting out. But it&#8217;s definitely not where you want to stay if you&#8217;re truly serious about blogging.</p>\n<p>Now that you&#8217;ve realized the shortcomings of the Blogger platform, it&#8217;s understandable you&#8217;d want to switch over to a reliable platform such as self-hosted WordPress, also known as WordPress.org</p>\n<p>Unlike Blogger, WordPress.org is a fully-featured content management system. WordPress gives you full control over your blog, lets you easily customize the look and feel of it, and add more features with plugins.</p>\n<p>Read our detailed <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/blogger-vs-wordpress-which-is-the-best-choice-expert-review/\">comparison between Blogger and WordPress</a> for more information.</p>\n<p>In this article, we’ll walk you through how to move your blog from Blogger to WordPress, step by step.</p>\n<p>Here’s a list of the steps we’ll cover through this guide:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"#signup\">Sign up for a web hosting account</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#domain\">Set up DNS &#8211; Blogger custom domain</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#install\">Install WordPress</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#export\">Export your Blogger blog</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#import\">Import Blogger to WordPress</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#permalinks\">Set up permalinks on WordPress</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#redirection\">Set up Blogger to WordPress redirection</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#other\">Move other content to WordPress</a></li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Understand the Goals: Blogger to WordPress Migration</h3>\n<p>Before we begin, it’s worth taking a moment to examine the goals we need to accomplish with your Blogger to WordPress migration.</p>\n<p><strong>Preserve Search Rankings and Traffic</strong>:</p>\n<p>Of course, nobody wants to move a blog if search rankings and traffic can’t be preserved after migration. In our tutorial, we’ll ensure that all your Blogger URLs are properly redirected to the right WordPress permalinks.</p>\n<p><strong>Set Up Proper Mobile Redirection</strong>:</p>\n<p>If you browse your Blogger.com blog on mobile, then you’ll see that Blogger automatically appends <strong>?m=1</strong> to your blog URL.</p>\n<p>For example, this is what your URL looks like if you access your site from a mobile device:</p>\n<p>http://example.blogspot.com/test-article.html<strong>?m=1</strong></p>\n<p>You shouldn’t leave your mobile users behind, so the goal is to make sure all mobile visits are also redirected to your WordPress site.</p>\n<p><strong>Move Feed Subscribers Properly</strong></p>\n<p>We’ll also explain how to move your feed subscribers properly.</p>\n<h3 id=\"signup\">Step 1. Sign Up for a Web Hosting Account</h3>\n<p>To run any website on the internet, you need to have a <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/difference-between-domain-name-and-web-hosting-revealed/\">domain name and web hosting</a>.</p>\n<p>A domain name is the web address of your site such as IsItWP.com or Google.com. And <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/hosting-reviews/\" title=\"Top 10 Web Hosting Companies of 2019 (Real Reviews, No B.S)\">web hosting</a> is where your site is hosted and your site files are stored.</p>\n<p>Blogger.com is a free hosted platform, meaning your blog is hosted on Blogger’s hosting server for free. However, when you move to WordPress, you’ll have to purchase <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/hosting-reviews/wordpress/\" title=\"The Best WordPress Hosting Companies of 2019 (Real Reviews, No B.S)\">WordPress hosting</a> space to host your blog.</p>\n<p>Now you might be wondering, &#8220;how much does it cost to purchase a domain name and web hosting?&#8221;</p>\n<p>A domain name normally costs around $14.99 per year and web hosting costs $7.99 per month. When you’re starting out with WordPress, the combined cost of domain and web hosting can seem like quite a lot.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/bluehost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/create-a-wordpress-account-on-bluehost.jpg\" alt=\"create a blog on bluehost\" width=\"775\" height=\"483\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-218254\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/create-a-wordpress-account-on-bluehost.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/create-a-wordpress-account-on-bluehost-300x187.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/create-a-wordpress-account-on-bluehost-768x479.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></a></p>\n<p>That’s why we’ve worked out a deal with <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/bluehost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Bluehost</a> to offer our users a <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/pick-best-domain-name/\" title=\"How to Pick the Best Domain Name (&#038; How to Get It for Free)\">free domain name</a>, free SSL, and 65% off on WordPress hosting.</p>\n<p>With our Bluehost deal, you can start your blog for as low as $2.75 per month.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/bluehost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"btn ltgreen light\">Click Here to Claim This Exclusive Bluehost Offer &raquo;</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/bluehost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Bluehost</a> is one of the largest hosting companies in the world. They are also an officially recommended hosting provider by WordPress.org.</p>\n<h3 id=\"domain\">Step 2. Using Custom Domain &#8211; Blogger to WordPress</h3>\n<div class=\"alert alert-warning\">You can skip this step if you&#8217;re NOT using a custom domain in Blogger</div>\n<p>If you’re using a custom domain name on your Blogger blog, like http://example.com instead of http://example.blogspot.com, you’ll want to update your domain name servers. Domain nameservers are usually a couple of URLs, like the ones below,  that you’ll get from your new web host.</p>\n<p>ns1.hostname.com</p>\n<p>ns2.hostname.com</p>\n<p>The steps to changing domain nameservers differ from one domain provider to another; however, the basic concept is the same. So, we’ll show you how to change DNS nameservers with <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/refer/domain-com/\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\" data-nojs=\"true\" >Domain.com</a> </p>\n<p>First off, log into your Domain.com account. Find the domain that you want to update and click on the <strong>Manage</strong> button.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/manage-nameservers.png\" alt=\"manage nameservers\" width=\"480\" height=\"480\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-230446\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/manage-nameservers.png 480w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/manage-nameservers-150x150.png 150w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/manage-nameservers-300x300.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 480px) 100vw, 480px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, click on DNS &amp; Nameservers.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/change-dns-and-nameservers.png\" alt=\"change-dns-and-nameservers\" width=\"694\" height=\"480\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-230447\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/change-dns-and-nameservers.png 694w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/change-dns-and-nameservers-300x207.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 694px) 100vw, 694px\" /></p>\n<p>To change the nameservers, click <strong>Edit</strong> next to Nameservers.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/edit-nameservers.png\" alt=\"edit nameservers\" width=\"740\" height=\"482\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-230448\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/edit-nameservers.png 740w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/01/edit-nameservers-300x195.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px\" /></p>\n<p>Then, fill in your new nameservers provided by your new web host, and click the <strong>Save</strong> button.</p>\n<p>Next, we&#8217;ll need to remove the custom domain setup in your Blogger.com account as well. </p>\n<p>Log into your Blogger.com account and navigate to <strong>Settings &raquo; Basic</strong>. Under the Publishing section, click on the cross icon to cancel the redirect.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/removeredirect.png\" alt=\"removeredirect\" width=\"550\" height=\"284\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-233502\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/removeredirect.png 550w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/removeredirect-300x155.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px\" /></p>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Make sure you flush your computer&#8217;s DNS cache after this step. Otherwise, you may still find your old Blogger.com blog, when you try to access your domain name from your browser. </p>\n<p>To clear DNS cache in Windows 10, you can search for Command Prompt in Windows, right-click it and select Run as Administrator.</p>\n<p>Then, run the following command: </p>\n<p><code>ipconfig /flushdns</code></p>\n<p>In Mac, click <strong>Applications &raquo; Utilities &raquo; Terminal</strong> and then run the following command: </p>\n<p><code>sudo killall -HUP mDNSResponder</code></p>\n<h3 id=\"install\">Step 3. Install WordPress</h3>\n<p>After signing up with Bluehost, the next step is to install WordPress.</p>\n<p>Upon choosing a hosting plan subscription, you&#8217;ll be prompted to choose a WordPress theme. You can pick just about anything during this step because you can always change your theme later (we’ll show you how to do this in a later step of this tutorial). The most important part is to start building your blog so go ahead and choose any theme for now just to get you rolling.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/pick-a-theme.png\" alt=\"pick a theme\" width=\"600\" height=\"276\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-218387\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/pick-a-theme.png 600w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/pick-a-theme-300x138.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></p>\n<p>You&#8217;ll be then asked to choose the name and tagline for your blog. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/create-a-new-wordpress-blog.jpg\" alt=\"create a new wordpress blog\" width=\"775\" height=\"472\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-218383\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/create-a-new-wordpress-blog.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/create-a-new-wordpress-blog-300x183.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/create-a-new-wordpress-blog-768x468.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>After specifying the details, click <strong>Next</strong>. Bluehost will now automatically install WordPress for you. Once it&#8217;s done, it&#8217;ll show you a screen like this:</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-installation-successful.jpg\" alt=\"wordpress installation successful\" width=\"775\" height=\"478\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-218385\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-installation-successful.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-installation-successful-300x185.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-installation-successful-768x474.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>You can log into your site by appending <strong>wp-admin</strong> to your URL. Here&#8217;s what your WordPress login URL should look like: </p>\n<p>http://example.com/wp-admin</p>\n<p>You can now log into your WordPress blog with the credentials sent to your email address. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-login.jpg\" alt=\"wordpress login\" width=\"775\" height=\"441\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-218386\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-login.jpg 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-login-300x171.jpg 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/wordpress-login-768x437.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<h3 id=\"export\">Step 4. Export Your Blogger Blog</h3>\n<p>To export your blog from Blogger, log into your Blogger.com profile and navigate to <strong>Settings &raquo; Other</strong>. In the Import &amp; back up section, click the <strong>Back up content</strong> button.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/export-blogger-blog.png\" alt=\"export-blogger-blog\" width=\"775\" height=\"399\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-220563\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/export-blogger-blog.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/export-blogger-blog-300x154.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/export-blogger-blog-768x395.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>This will trigger a modal popup in which you’ll be asked to make a backup of your blog. Click the <strong>Save to your computer</strong> button.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/save-blogger-export-file.png\" alt=\"save blogger export file\" width=\"541\" height=\"213\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-220569\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/save-blogger-export-file.png 541w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/save-blogger-export-file-300x118.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 541px) 100vw, 541px\" /></p>\n<h3 id=\"import\">Step 5. Import Blogger to WordPress</h3>\n<p>After downloading the export file from Blogger, the next step is to import the file into your new WordPress site.</p>\n<p>Log into your WordPress dashboard, go to <strong>Tools &raquo; Import</strong>. Just below the Blogger option, click <strong>Install Now</strong>. Then, click <strong>Run Importer</strong>.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/install-blogger-importer.png\" alt=\"install-blogger-importer\" width=\"650\" height=\"230\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-220566\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/install-blogger-importer.png 650w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/install-blogger-importer-300x106.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, choose the file you&#8217;ve just downloaded from Blogger. Then import it into your WordPress site. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/import-blogger-files-into-wordpress.png\" alt=\"import blogger files into wordpress\" width=\"760\" height=\"222\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-220565\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/import-blogger-files-into-wordpress.png 760w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/import-blogger-files-into-wordpress-300x88.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 760px) 100vw, 760px\" /></p>\n<p>After importing the files, you&#8217;ll be asked whether you need to create new users on your site or assign the posts to your existing users. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/import-blogger-assign-authors.png\" alt=\"import blogger assign authors\" width=\"571\" height=\"315\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-220564\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/import-blogger-assign-authors.png 571w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/import-blogger-assign-authors-300x165.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 571px) 100vw, 571px\" /></p>\n<h3 id=\"permalinks\">Step 6. Set Up Permalinks on WordPress</h3>\n<p>A permalink, or permanent link, is the full URL to your individual pages of your WordPress site.</p>\n<p>When migrating your blog from Blogger to WordPress, it’s essential to keep your permalink structure identical for proper redirection.</p>\n<p>WordPress allows you to choose your preferred permalink structure for your blog. To choose your permalinks&#8217; structure, go to <strong>Settings &raquo; Permalinks</strong>. In the <strong>Custom Structure</strong> field, specify your structure as follows:</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/permalinks-structure.png\" alt=\"permalinks structure\" width=\"775\" height=\"387\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-220567\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/permalinks-structure.png 775w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/permalinks-structure-300x150.png 300w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/permalinks-structure-768x384.png 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 775px) 100vw, 775px\" /></p>\n<p>/%year%/%monthnum%/%postname%.html</p>\n<p>The above configuration makes your permalinks look similar to that of Blogger.com. But for proper redirection, we need to make our permalinks <strong>identical</strong>.</p>\n<p>For example, here’s what your post URL looked like on Blogger:</p>\n<p>http://example.blogspot.com/2018/06/the-unconventional-guide-to-home-tech.html</p>\n<p>If you don’t make the permalinks identical, here’s what the same post URL will look like after moving to WordPress.</p>\n<p>http://example.com/2018/06/the-unconventional-guide-to-home-tech-gadgets-for-beginners.html</p>\n<p>To make your Blogger post URL identical in WordPress, all you have to do is open a simple text editor application such as Notepad or TextEdit. Copy the below code into your text editor and save it as a PHP file. Give a name to your file like <strong>fix.php</strong>. Then upload the file to your WordPress folder, which also known as the root directory.</p>\n<pre class=\"brush: php; title: ; notranslate\">\r\n&lt;?php\r\nrequire_once(\'wp-load.php\');\r\n$res = $wpdb-&gt;get_results(&quot;SELECT post_id, meta_value FROM $wpdb-&gt;postmeta WHERE meta_key = \'blogger_permalink\'&quot;);\r\n$wpdb-&gt;print_error();\r\nforeach ($res as $row){\r\n$slug = explode(&quot;/&quot;,$row-&gt;meta_value);\r\n$slug = explode(&quot;.&quot;,$slug[3]);\r\n$wpdb-&gt;query(&quot;UPDATE $wpdb-&gt;posts SET post_name =\'&quot; . $slug[0] . &quot;\' WHERE ID = $row-&gt;post_id&quot;);\r\n$wpdb-&gt;print_error();\r\n}\r\necho &quot;DONE&quot;;\r\n?&gt;\r\n</pre>\n<p>If you’ve uploaded the file in the right directory, then you can execute the script by opening its URL from the browser: <strong>http://example.com/fix.php</strong></p>\n<p>When executing the script, the only output you can see is <strong>Done</strong>.</p>\n<h3 id=\"redirection\">Step 7. Set Up Blogger to WordPress Redirection</h3>\n<p>Now that you’ve set up permalinks for your WordPress blog, let’s redirect your blogger posts to WordPress. For redirecting your Blogger blog to WordPress, we’ll be using a free plugin, <a href=\"http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/blogger-to-wordpress-redirection/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Blogger to WordPress Redirection</a>.</p>\n<p>Install and activate the plugin on your newly-installed WordPress site. Then go to <strong>Tools &raquo; Blogger to WordPress Redirection</strong>.</p>\n<p>You’ll be directed to the plugin configuration page. Click the <strong>Start Configuration</strong> button to generate the code for Blogger.com.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/blogger-to-wordpress-redirection.png\" alt=\"blogger to wordpress redirection\" width=\"680\" height=\"298\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-220560\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/blogger-to-wordpress-redirection.png 680w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/blogger-to-wordpress-redirection-300x131.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 680px) 100vw, 680px\" /></p>\n<p>You can now find a list of blogs from where you’ve imported content. Click <strong>Get Code</strong> next to the correct blog and copy the code.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/blogger-to-wordpress-get-code.png\" alt=\"blogger to wordpress get code\" width=\"651\" height=\"486\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-220559\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/blogger-to-wordpress-get-code.png 651w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/blogger-to-wordpress-get-code-300x224.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 651px) 100vw, 651px\" /></p>\n<p>Now go back to your Blogger.com profile and click the <strong>Edit HTML</strong> button.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/edit-html-blogger.png\" alt=\"edit html blogger\" width=\"748\" height=\"369\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-220562\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/edit-html-blogger.png 748w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/edit-html-blogger-300x148.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 748px) 100vw, 748px\" /></p>\n<p>Paste the copied code and click <strong>Save Theme</strong>.</p>\n<p>By default, Blogger.com redirects your mobile visitors to the mobile-friendly version of your blog by appending ?m=1 to the URL. For proper mobile redirection, we need to disable this feature.</p>\n<p>To disable the feature, click the <strong>Back</strong> button in your Edit HTML page. You can now find a gear button below the mobile preview of your Blogger theme. </p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/blogger-mobile-redirection.png\" alt=\"blogger mobile redirection\" width=\"748\" height=\"368\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-220558\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/blogger-mobile-redirection.png 748w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/blogger-mobile-redirection-300x148.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 748px) 100vw, 748px\" /></p>\n<p>This will show you a modal popup where you’ll be asked whether you want to show a mobile version of your theme. Select <strong>No</strong> and click <strong>Save</strong>.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/choose-mobile-theme.png\" alt=\"choose mobile theme\" width=\"580\" height=\"274\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-220561\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/choose-mobile-theme.png 580w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/choose-mobile-theme-300x142.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 580px) 100vw, 580px\" /></p>\n<h3 id=\"other\">Step 8. Move Other Content to WordPress</h3>\n<p>After moving your blog posts, you can go ahead and move your pages and other content to WordPress.</p>\n<p><strong>Pages</strong>:</p>\n<p>Go to your WordPress dashboard and create a new page. Copy the HTML code of your Blogger page, and paste it into the newly created page on WordPress.</p>\n<p>On Blogger, the URL of your page looked like this: example.com/p/page.html</p>\n<p>On WordPress, here’s how the same page will look after migration: example.com/page</p>\n<p>To redirect your pages properly, you can use the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/redirection/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\">Redirection plugin</a> in WordPress.</p>\n<p><strong>Widgets</strong>:</p>\n<p>If you want to retain your Blogger.com widgets in WordPress, then you’ll need to copy the HTML code and paste it into the sidebar widgets of your WordPress site by navigating to <strong>Appearance &raquo; Widgets</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Feeds</strong>:</p>\n<p>To redirect your feeds, navigate to <strong>Settings &raquo; Other</strong> in your Blogger.com profile. Click on the <strong>Add</strong> option next to <strong>Post Feed Redirect URL</strong>. Then specify your WordPress feed as follows: http://example.com/feed</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/post-feed-redirect-url.png\" alt=\"post feed redirect url\" width=\"603\" height=\"340\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-220568\" srcset=\"https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/post-feed-redirect-url.png 603w, https://www.isitwp.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/post-feed-redirect-url-300x169.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 603px) 100vw, 603px\" /></p>\n<h3>What’s Next After Migration?</h3>\n<p>Below are a few essential things you need to do immediately on your WordPress blog after migration:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Give a unique look to your site with the <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/top-wordpress-themes/\">perfect WordPress theme</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/install-google-analytics-wordpress-site/\">Install Google Analytics in WordPress</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/add-contact-form-wordpress-website/\" title=\"How to Create a Contact Form on WordPress (the Easy Way)\">Add a contact form to your WordPress site</a></li>\n<li>Provide bullet proof security by installing some of the <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-wordpress-security-plugins-compared/\">best WordPress security plugins</a></li>\n<li>Improve WordPress SEO with the <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/best-seo-tools-to-grow-your-site-traffic/\">best WordPress SEO plugins</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Here’s a list of <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/top-wordpress-plugins/\">popular WordPress plugins</a> that you may find useful.</p>\n<p>That’s it!</p>\n<p>If you ever plan to switch your domain, then check out this guide on <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/move-wordpress-to-new-domain-name/\" title=\"How to Properly Move WordPress to a New Domain Name\">how to properly move WordPress to a new domain name</a>.</p>\n<p>We hope this guide helped you move your blog from Blogger to WordPress. If you enjoyed this article, then check out our guide on <a href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/must-have-wordpress-plugins-for-business-websites/\">must have WordPress plugins for business websites</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/move-from-blogger-to-wordpress-resolved/\">The 2019’s Guide to Moving a Blog From Blogger to WordPress (Resolved)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com\">IsItWP - WordPress Technology Lookup Tool</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:68:\"https://www.isitwp.com/move-from-blogger-to-wordpress-resolved/feed/\";s