ou could see how people are truly interacting with your website? Sessions and bounce rates only tell you so much. How much of your content are they really reading? With the latest release of MonsterInsights, now you can see how far people are scrolling on your website, so you can get a better [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/announcing-scroll-tracking-front-end-page-insights-and-more/\">Announcing Scroll Tracking, Front-End Page Insights, and More</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Keri Engel\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5173:\"<p>Ever wish you could see how people are truly interacting with your website? Sessions and bounce rates only tell you so much. How much of your content are they really reading?</p>\n<p>With the latest release of MonsterInsights, now you can see how far people are scrolling on your website, so you can get a better picture of your visitor engagement and make data-driven decisions to grow your business.</p>\n<p>Let’s take a closer look at what’s new in MonsterInsights 7.6&#8230;</p>\n<h3>New Automatic Scroll Tracking</h3>\n<p>Google Analytics has no automatic, native way to set up scroll tracking. But MonsterInsights 7.6 will automatically enable this feature for you &#8211; no setup or configuration required.</p>\n<p>Your scroll tracking stats can be found in the MonsterInsights Publishers Report, next to the Interests section.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/scroll-tracking-in-wordpress.jpg\" alt=\"scroll tracking in wordpress with monsterinsights\" width=\"560\" height=\"324\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-199030\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/scroll-tracking-in-wordpress.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/scroll-tracking-in-wordpress-300x174.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>Scroll tracking can not only give you a better picture of how your visitors are interacting with your content, but also help you decide the best place for your important <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/how-to-create-the-perfect-call-to-action/\" rel=\"noopener\" target=\"_blank\">calls to action</a>, <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-track-adsense-in-google-analytics-to-optimize-your-revenue/\">ads</a>, and more.</p>\n<p>Read our <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/docs/scroll-tracking-and-reporting/\">scroll tracking documentation</a> for details on how to use Scroll Tracking and view scroll percentage for each page.</p>\n<h3>View Page Insights on the Front End of Your Site</h3>\n<p>MonsterInsights 7.6 includes a new feature call Admin Bar Page Insights</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/front-end-page-insights-min.jpg\" alt=\"front end page insights for wordpress using monsterinsights\" width=\"560\" height=\"330\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-199033\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/front-end-page-insights-min.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/front-end-page-insights-min-300x177.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>Now you can easily see your last 30 day stats for any page at a glance.</p>\n<p>This will make it easier than ever to make content decisions quickly, without having to spend a lot of time generating reports in Google Analytics. Seeing your page stats at a glance will help you:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>come up with content ideas based on what your audience loves</li>\n<li>decide which content needs to be deleted or optimized to boost your traffic</li>\n<li>create the products and premium offerings your visitors are looking for</li>\n</ul>\n<p>You can view our <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/docs/admin-bar-page-insights/\">admin bar page insights doc</a> for more details.</p>\n<h3>New &#8211; Meet the MonsterInsights Team!</h3>\n<p>With MonsterInsights 7.6, we’ve also added a new About page to our plugin menu. The MonsterInsights team is growing fast, and we wanted to take this opportunity to show off the work of the each individual on our team and connect more with our users.</p>\n<p>You can see our developers, writers, and support team on the MonsterInsights About page and learn all the insider behind-the-scenes info on MonsterInsights.</p>\n<p>After updating to the latest version, you can check it out at <strong>Insights &raquo; About Us</strong>.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/about-the-monsterinsights-team-min.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"560\" height=\"247\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-199036\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/about-the-monsterinsights-team-min.png 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/about-the-monsterinsights-team-min-300x132.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>Leave a comment here or <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/contact/\">reach out</a> and let us know what you think!</p>\n<p>That’s it for today! We have plenty more amazing features planned for you, so stay tuned for upcoming announcements. Be sure to subscribe to our newsletter and follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/monsterinsights\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Twitter</a> and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/monsterinsights\" rel=\"noopener nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">Facebook</a> to be the first to know.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/announcing-scroll-tracking-front-end-page-insights-and-more/\">Announcing Scroll Tracking, Front-End Page Insights, and More</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:97:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/announcing-scroll-tracking-front-end-page-insights-and-more/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"How to Create a Membership Website That Makes Money (2019)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:145:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-create-a-membership-website/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-create-a-membership-website\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:75:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-create-a-membership-website/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sun, 28 Apr 2019 19:32:41 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"monetization\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"wordpress membership site\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:28:\"membership plugins wordpress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:41:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/?p=198572\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:601:\"<p>Do you want to create a membership website that makes money? Membership websites let you add content behind a locked gate so you can earn money by making people pay for access. Basically, they require people to buy a membership to view the gated content. Creating a membership site is a very popular online business [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-create-a-membership-website/\">How to Create a Membership Website That Makes Money (2019)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Sunita Rai\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25265:\"<p>Do you want to create a membership website that makes money? Membership websites let you add content behind a locked gate so you can earn money by making people pay for access. Basically, they require people to buy a membership to view the gated content.</p>\n<p>Creating a membership site is a very popular online business model nowadays, and for good reason. Paid online courses, premium support forums, and webinars are among most profitable sites on the internet.</p>\n<p>In this article, we’ll show you how to easily create a membership website step-by-step. Let’s get started with the table of contents:</p>\n<p><strong>Table of Contents</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"#choosesiteplatform\">Choosing the right platform for your membership website</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#setupwpmembershipsite\">Setting up your WordPress membership site</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#setupmemberpress\">Setting up your membership plugin</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#payment\">Adding payment methods</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#memebrshiplevels\">Adding membership levels</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#accessrules\">Setting up access rules for your membership plans</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#createcontent\">Creating members-only content</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#pricingpage\">Creating a pricing page</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#signuplogin\">Adding sign up and login forms</a></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Now, we’ll walk you through these steps one-by-one.</p>\n<h3 id=\"choosesiteplatform\">Step 1: Choosing the Right Platform for Your Membership Site</h3>\n<p>The first step to making a membership website is to choose the right website platform. While there’re many generic website builders on the market, you&#8217;ll need a platform that specifically fulfills the needs of a membership site.</p>\n<p>Some of the most important features you’ll need for your membership website are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Membership Management – option to create different types of memberships, and to add and manage members.</li>\n<li>User Registration and Member Profiles – frontend options for your users to sign up or login to your site, and to access their member profiles.</li>\n<li>Content Restriction – options to hide your content from general audiences.</li>\n<li>Payment Options – options to integrate payment gateways to accept online payments.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>You can add these features in almost any platform; however, most will require technical skills. If you don’t have any coding skills, you may need to hire a developer.</p>\n<p>Luckily, WordPress comes with an easy way to build membership websites. By using powerful WordPress membership plugins, you can quickly set up a membership website and start selling with little-to-no technical skills.</p>\n<p>There’re many free and premium membership plugins, so you may get confused trying to figure out which one to use. Check out our detailed comparison post on the <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/best-wordpress-membership-plugins-compared/\">best WordPress membership plugins</a> to make your selection more easily.</p>\n<p>In this article, we’ll use the <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/memberpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">MemberPress</a> plugin to create a membership website. It’s the most popular WordPress membership plugin in the world.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/memberpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-194244\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/memberspresswordpressmembershipplugin.png\" alt=\"MemberPress Best WordPress Membership Plugin\" width=\"620\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/memberspresswordpressmembershipplugin.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/memberspresswordpressmembershipplugin-300x145.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>MemberPress comes with advanced features that let you create multiple membership levels, restrict access to content, accept payments, and more. Also, it integrates well with email marketing services and other useful tools like bbPress and Affiliate Royale.</p>\n<p>With that said, let’s start setting up your WordPress membership website.</p>\n<h3 id=\"setupwpmembershipsite\">Step 2: Setting Up Your WordPress Membership Site</h3>\n<p>In addition to a membership plugin, you’ll need a domain a name, a web hosting account, and an SSL certificate to create a membership site with WordPress.</p>\n<p>A domain name is the web address of your membership site — for example, monsterinsights.com or google.com. A web hosting account is where your website files are stored online. And, an SSL certificate is required to make secure transactions.</p>\n<p>You can buy a domain name for around $14.99 per year, web hosting for $7.99 per month, and an SSL certificate for $49.99 per year.</p>\n<p>If you add these amounts together, the total cost would be very high, especially if you&#8217;re a beginner without a big budget.</p>\n<p>Fortunately, <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/bluehost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Bluehost</a> is offering an exclusive deal to our customers. Now you can enjoy 60% off on WordPress hosting, get a free domain, and nab a free SSL certificate along with it. That means you can get all 3 of these essentials for just $2.75 per month.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/bluehost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-185172\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/bluehostwordpresshosting.jpg\" alt=\"Bluehost Best WordPress Hosting\" width=\"620\" height=\"375\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/bluehostwordpresshosting.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/bluehostwordpresshosting-300x181.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Bluehost is one of the oldest and most popular web hosting companies in the world. They’re officially recommended by both WordPress.org and the world&#8217;s most popular unofficial WordPress resource website, <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">WPBeginner</a>.</p>\n<p>To get started, you need to choose a domain name and sign up for your hosting account. Once done, the next step is usually to <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/how-to-install-wordpress/ target=_blank\">install WordPress</a>; but you won’t need to do it manually because it comes pre-installed on your Bluehost account.</p>\n<p>Therefore, the next step is to install and configure your membership plugin. Let&#8217;s do that now.</p>\n<h3 id=\"setupmemberpress\">Step 3: Setting Up Your Membership Plugin</h3>\n<p>As mentioned above, we’ve chosen the MemberPress plugin for this tutorial.</p>\n<p>First, you&#8217;ll need to install and activate the <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/refer/memberpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">MemberPress</a> plugin. For detailed instructions, see our guide on <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/step-by-step-guide-to-install-a-wordpress-plugin-for-beginners/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">how to install a WordPress plugin</a>.</p>\n<p>Once the plugin is activated, you’ll see a notification bar with a link to the plugin&#8217;s Options page for configuring.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198632\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/go-to-memberpress-options.png\" alt=\"Go to MemberPress Options Page\" width=\"620\" height=\"102\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/go-to-memberpress-options.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/go-to-memberpress-options-300x49.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Simply click on the ‘options page’ link, and it’ll take you to your MemberPress options page. Alternately, you can go to <strong>MemberPress » Options</strong> to access the plugin&#8217;s settings.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198633\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/memberpressoptions.png\" alt=\"MemberPress Options Page\" width=\"620\" height=\"449\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/memberpressoptions.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/memberpressoptions-300x217.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>From this page, you can configure all your plugin settings.</p>\n<h3 id=\"payment\">Step 4: Adding Payment Methods</h3>\n<p>Payments are of vital importance. Click on the ‘Payments’ tab in the Options page to configure the payment gateways for your membership website.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198634\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/memberpresspaymentoptions.png\" alt=\"MemberPress Payment Options\" width=\"620\" height=\"290\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/memberpresspaymentoptions.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/memberpresspaymentoptions-300x140.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>MemberPress, by default, allows you to use PayPal (Standard and Express), Stripe, and Authorize.net as your payment gateway. You can configure one or multiple gateways for your website.</p>\n<h3 id=\"memebrshiplevels\">Step 5: Adding Membership Levels</h3>\n<p>Once you’ve configured the settings, the next step is to add membership levels that people can purchase. MemberPress allows you to create unlimited membership levels, each with different pricing, features, and content access.</p>\n<p>Go to <strong>MemberPress » Memberships</strong> from your dashboard menu and click the ‘Add New’ button.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198635\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addnewmembership.png\" alt=\"Add New Membership with MemberPress\" width=\"620\" height=\"237\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addnewmembership.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addnewmembership-300x115.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>On the next screen, you’ll see a page that looks similar to the Classic WordPress editor. On this page, you can create a membership level.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198636\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addmembershipcontent.png\" alt=\"Add Membership Content in WordPress\" width=\"620\" height=\"322\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addmembershipcontent.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addmembershipcontent-300x156.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Enter a title and add a description for your membership level in the editor. Next, set the price, choose a billing type, and set an access time or expiry date from the ‘Membership Terms’ section on the right side of the page.</p>\n<p>After that, scroll down to the ‘Membership Options’ section to configure the registration, permissions, price box, and more.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198637\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/membershipoptions.png\" alt=\"Membership Options for registration and more\" width=\"620\" height=\"287\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/membershipoptions.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/membershipoptions-300x139.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Once you’ve configured all the settings, go ahead and publish your membership level.</p>\n<h3 id=\"accessrules\">Step 6: Setting Up Access Rules for Your Membership Plans</h3>\n<p>Now that you’ve created membership levels, the next step is to set up rules to define which content can be accessed for those different membership levels.</p>\n<p>Navigate to <strong>MemberPress » Rules</strong> and click on the ‘Add New’ button.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198638\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addnewmemberspressrule.png\" alt=\"Add New Membership Rule\" width=\"620\" height=\"279\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addnewmemberspressrule.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addnewmemberspressrule-300x135.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>On the next screen, you can create a new rule to link your content to the membership levels.</p>\n<p>For example, you can select all the content under a particular category to be accessible by users with a specific subscription plan.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198639\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/setupnewmembershiprule.png\" alt=\"Set Up Membership Rule in WordPress\" width=\"620\" height=\"427\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/setupnewmembershiprule.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/setupnewmembershiprule-300x207.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>In the screenshot above, we’ve selected all the content in the ‘Advanced WordPress Guide’ category to be available only to members with a Platinum or Gold subscription plan.</p>\n<p>Next, you&#8217;ll see the ‘Drip/Expiration’ box. Enabling the drip option will allow you to gradually release content; whereas the expiration option will let you choose the time in which the content will no longer be available.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198640\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/dripandexpirationoptionsmemberpress.png\" alt=\"Drip and Expiration Options in MemberPress\" width=\"620\" height=\"205\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/dripandexpirationoptionsmemberpress.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/dripandexpirationoptionsmemberpress-300x99.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Once you’ve configured all the options, save your rule. You can create more rules by repeating those same steps.</p>\n<h3 id=\"createcontent\">Step 7: Creating Members-Only Content</h3>\n<p>The next step is to create members-only content.</p>\n<p>Members-only content refers to the gated content which cannot be accessed by the general public and is available only to your registered members.</p>\n<p>You can add content with posts or pages, just like you would on a typical WordPress website. Below, we’ll create a post with the ‘Advanced WordPress Guide’ category to match the rule we created in the last step.</p>\n<p>Simply create a new post and add content to it. Then, select the ‘Advanced WordPress Guide’ category.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198641\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addcontentandchoosecategory.png\" alt=\"Add Content to a Post and Choose a Category \" width=\"620\" height=\"368\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addcontentandchoosecategory.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addcontentandchoosecategory-300x178.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>After that, scroll down to the ‘MemberPress Unauthorized Access’ section. You can set up what non-members (non-registered users) will see when they try to access this content.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198642\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/unauthorizedaccessoptionsonpost.png\" alt=\"Unauthorized Access Option in a WordPress Post\" width=\"620\" height=\"341\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/unauthorizedaccessoptionsonpost.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/unauthorizedaccessoptionsonpost-300x165.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Once you’ve added your content and configured everything, you can publish your page. After that, you can visit <strong>Posts » All Posts</strong> and see which content is protected for certain membership holders.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198643\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/members-onlycontentmemberpress.png\" alt=\"Members-only Content in WordPress\" width=\"620\" height=\"205\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/members-onlycontentmemberpress.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/members-onlycontentmemberpress-300x99.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<h3 id=\"pricingpage\">Step 8: Creating a Pricing Page</h3>\n<p>Next, you&#8217;ll need to create a pricing page where your site visitors can choose a membership plan and sign up for that plan. The MemberPress plugin lets you create a pricing page easily using its Group options.</p>\n<p>Visit <strong>MemberPress » Groups</strong> from your admin panel and click on the ‘Add New’ button.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198644\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addnewgroupforpricingpage.png\" alt=\"Add New Group for Pricing Page\" width=\"620\" height=\"290\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addnewgroupforpricingpage.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addnewgroupforpricingpage-300x140.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Enter your group title first. You can name it ‘Pricing Plans’ or something similar because it’ll ultimately serve as your pricing page.</p>\n<p>Next, scroll down to the ‘Group Options’ section and add the memberships you want to show on your pricing page. Also choose your pricing page&#8217;s theme.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198645\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/memberpressgroupoptions.png\" alt=\"MemberPress Group Options\" width=\"620\" height=\"451\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/memberpressgroupoptions.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/memberpressgroupoptions-300x218.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Once you&#8217;ve configured all the options, click the ‘Publish’ button.</p>\n<p>If you want to see how your pricing page looks, you can preview it. Here’s how a MemberPress pricing page will appear on the default Twenty Nineteen theme:</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198646\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/pricingpagedemo.png\" alt=\"MemberPress Pricing Page Demo in Twenty Nineteen theme\" width=\"620\" height=\"344\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/pricingpagedemo.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/pricingpagedemo-300x166.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>After that, you&#8217;ll need to direct unauthorized users (non-members) to the pricing page.</p>\n<p>Visit <strong>MemberPress » Groups</strong> page and copy the URL of the group you created before.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198647\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/copygroupurlmemberpress.png\" alt=\"Copy the group URL to redirect non-members to Pricing Page\" width=\"620\" height=\"205\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/copygroupurlmemberpress.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/copygroupurlmemberpress-300x99.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, go to the <strong>MemberPress » Options</strong> page and go down to the ‘Unauthorized Access’ section.</p>\n<p>Now, check the box next to ‘Redirect unauthorized visitors to a specific URL’ and then paste the group URL you copied earlier.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198648\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/redirectunauthorizedvisitorstopricingpage.png\" alt=\"Redirect unauthorized users to Pricing Page\" width=\"620\" height=\"355\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/redirectunauthorizedvisitorstopricingpage.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/redirectunauthorizedvisitorstopricingpage-300x172.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>After that, click on the ‘Update Options’ button at the bottom. Now your non-members and unauthorized visitors will be redirected to your pricing page whenever they try to access your hidden premium content.</p>\n<h3 id=\"signuplogin\">Step 9: Adding Sign Up and Login Forms</h3>\n<p>Now you’ve set up everything, the final step is to add sign up and login forms to your site. The MemberPress plugin lets you make a website with user accounts and profiles with ease.</p>\n<p>First, you can add a user login form using a widget. Go to <strong>Appearance » Widegts</strong> from your admin panel and add the ‘MemberPress Login’ widget to a widget-ready area.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198649\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addmembershiploginwidgettoyoursite.png\" alt=\"Add MemberPress Login widget to Your website\" width=\"620\" height=\"252\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addmembershiploginwidgettoyoursite.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addmembershiploginwidgettoyoursite-300x122.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, you&#8217;ll need to add your pricing page URL to your navigation menu so your website visitors can sign up for a membership plan.</p>\n<p>Visit <strong>Appearance » Menus</strong> page from your dashboard. Create a new menu or choose an existing menu. Next, select ‘Pricing Plans’ under the ‘Groups’ tab and then click on the ‘Add to Menu’ button.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-198650\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addpricingplanspagetowpmenu.jpg\" alt=\"Add Pricing Page to WordPress Menu\" width=\"620\" height=\"501\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addpricingplanspagetowpmenu.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/addpricingplanspagetowpmenu-300x242.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Once your pricing page appears below the menu structure, you can drag it to rearrange its position. Once satisfied, don’t forget to save your menu.</p>\n<p>That’s it! Now you can open your website and preview it in action.</p>\n<h3>Optimizing Your WordPress Membership Website for Growth</h3>\n<p>Now that you’ve created a WordPress membership website, your next task is to optimize it for more traffic and more transactions. Luckily, there’re plenty of plugins and tools to help you out.</p>\n<p>You can use the following plugins and tools to grow your membership website:</p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\">1. MonsterInsights</a></strong>: The best Google Analytics plugin for WordPress. You can use this plugin to get complete insights into your users and eCommerce transactions.</p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/ target=\">2. OptinMonster</a></strong>: The best lead generation software on the market. It helps you build your email list faster and increase your website conversions.</p>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://www.wpforms.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">3. WPForms</a></strong>: The absolute best WordPress form builder plugin available. You can use this plugin to <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-create-a-contact-form-in-wordpress-the-simple-way/\">create a simple contact form</a> as well as interactive <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-create-a-survey-in-wordpress/&quot;\">surveys</a> and conversational forms, like Typeform.</p>\n<p>If you want to add more features to your website, check out our complete list of <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/must-have-wordpress-plugins-and-tools-for-business-websites/\">must-have WordPress plugins and tools for business websites</a>.</p>\n<p>We hope this article helped you create a fully functional membership website that earns money. You may also want to read our guide on <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-create-a-free-business-email-address/\">how to create a free business email address</a>.</p>\n<p>And don’t forget to follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Twitter</a> and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook</a> for more helpful Google Analytics tips.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-create-a-membership-website/\">How to Create a Membership Website That Makes Money (2019)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:72:\"https://www.monst