";s:15:\"monsterinsights\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"make money online\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"membership site\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"https://wpforms.com/?p=469852\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:595:\"<p>Are you trying to figure out how to create a membership site with WordPress? Membership sites let you charge users for access to restricted content so you can skyrocket your website&#8217;s revenue. In this article, we&#8217;ll show you exactly how to easily create a membership site using WordPress. What Is a WordPress Membership Site? A [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/create-a-membership-site-with-wordpress/\">How to Create a Membership Site with WordPress (Easily)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Lisa Gennaro\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:23203:\"<p>Are you trying to figure out how to create a membership site with WordPress?</p>\n<p>Membership sites let you charge users for access to restricted content so you can skyrocket your website&#8217;s revenue.</p>\n<p>In this article, we&#8217;ll show you exactly how to easily create a membership site using WordPress.</p>\n<h3>What Is a WordPress Membership Site?</h3>\n<p>A membership site invites visitors to pay to access certain areas or content on your site. It lets you restrict access to all or some of your site’s content, downloads, forums, online courses, support team, and more.</p>\n<p>Membership sites are an increasingly popular and easy way for people to <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/make-money-online/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">make money online</a> with their websites.</p>\n<h3>What Are the Benefits of Creating a Membership Site?</h3>\n<p>There are a lot of reasons why you may want to consider having your own members only area of your website. Here are some of the most popular benefits of creating a membership site:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>More Income.</strong> Membership websites use a recurring billing model, meaning you can generate a steady stream of income that grows every month when more and more visitors register. This can help boost your income, especially if you&#8217;re already using affiliate sales and advertising.</li>\n<li><strong>Less Work.</strong> Put your content to work for you. Membership sites are a fantastic way to grow your passive income by creating premium content once, then adding to it only if you choose to. If you create a great membership site once, you don&#8217;t have to do much more to continue to grow it unless you decide to update your content or interact with your members.</li>\n<li><strong>Establish Authority.</strong> When you restrict content to a membership plan, visitors will easily understand that your premium content is valuable and that you are a master on the subject.</li>\n<li><strong>Grow Your Email List.</strong> When you add registered users to your email list, you&#8217;ll fill it with engaged visitors who are already familiar with your site and more likely to interact with your emails. This will help boost your <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/best-email-marketing-service-providers-with-free-options/\">email marketing</a> efforts.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>What Is the Best Membership Plugin for WordPress?</h3>\n<p>There are a lot of great membership plugins for WordPress.</p>\n<p>With the WPForms <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/user-registration-addon/\">User Registration Addon,</a> you can create registration forms to let your visitors register for a WordPress account easily. And you can automatically add them to your email list, send them welcome emails, and even activate their accounts.</p>\n<p>However, if you&#8217;re looking for a more comprehensive membership website plugin, you should use <a title=\"MemberPress\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/memberpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">MemberPress.</a></p>\n<p><a title=\"MemberPress\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/memberpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-470257\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/best-membership-plugin-memberpress.jpg\" alt=\"best membership plugin memberpress\" width=\"562\" height=\"586\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/best-membership-plugin-memberpress.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/best-membership-plugin-memberpress-288x300.jpg 288w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></a></p>\n<p>We recommend it because it&#8217;s easy to use, works great with WPForms, and is one of the most popular membership plugins on the market.</p>\n<h3>How to Create a Membership Site with WordPress</h3>\n<p>Let&#8217;s go ahead and take a look at how to create a membership site with WordPress + MemberPress.</p>\n<p><strong>Step 1: Set Up The <a title=\"MemberPress\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/memberpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">MemberPress</a> Plugin.</strong></p>\n<p>You&#8217;ll want to start by installing and activating the MemberPress plugin. Here&#8217;s a step by step guide on <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/step-by-step-guide-to-install-a-wordpress-plugin-for-beginners/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">how to install a WordPress plugin</a>.</p>\n<p>Next, click on the link to the plugin&#8217;s options page in the Dashboard notification.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-469866\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/wordpress-membership-site-theme-memberpress-setup.jpg\" alt=\"wordpress membership site theme memberpress setup\" width=\"562\" height=\"92\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/wordpress-membership-site-theme-memberpress-setup.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/wordpress-membership-site-theme-memberpress-setup-300x49.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>In addition, you can also access this page by going to <strong>MemberPress » Options.</strong></p>\n<p>Now, configure all of the settings to your liking.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-469867\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/wordpress-paid-membership-plugin-memberpress-options.jpg\" alt=\"wordpress paid membership plugin memberpress options\" width=\"562\" height=\"407\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/wordpress-paid-membership-plugin-memberpress-options.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/wordpress-paid-membership-plugin-memberpress-options-300x217.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p><strong>Step 2: Set Up Your Payment Methods</strong></p>\n<p>Next, click on the Payments tab in the options page to set up the payment gateways you want to use on your membership site.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-469868\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/how-to-build-a-membership-website-memberpress.jpg\" alt=\"how to build a membership website memberpress\" width=\"562\" height=\"263\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/how-to-build-a-membership-website-memberpress.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/how-to-build-a-membership-website-memberpress-300x140.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>MemberPress lets you use PayPal, Stripe, and Authorize.net as your payment gateway. Feel free to setup multiple payment gateways or just stick with one.</p>\n<p>For an in-depth comparison on the 2 most popular options, check out our article <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/stripe-vs-paypal-which-one-is-better/\">Stripe vs Paypal</a>.</p>\n<p><strong>Step 3: Create Membership Levels</strong></p>\n<p>Now that your MemberPress settings are all configured, the next step is to create membership levels for visitors to purchase.</p>\n<p>Each level can have different pricing, features, and content. Luckily, you can make unlimited membership levels with MemberPress.</p>\n<p>To do this, go to <strong>MemberPress » Memberships</strong> from the left hand Dashboard menu, and after that click on the <strong>Add New</strong> button.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-469901\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/set-up-a-membership-wordpress-plugin.jpg\" alt=\"set up a membership wordpress plugin\" width=\"562\" height=\"216\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/set-up-a-membership-wordpress-plugin.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/set-up-a-membership-wordpress-plugin-300x115.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, enter a title and description for your membership level in the editor. Then, set the price, billing type, and access time from the <strong>Membership Terms</strong> section on the right.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-469904\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/wordpress-paid-membership-plugin-add-new.jpg\" alt=\"wordpress paid membership plugin add new\" width=\"562\" height=\"293\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/wordpress-paid-membership-plugin-add-new.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/wordpress-paid-membership-plugin-add-new-300x156.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>After that you&#8217;ll want to scroll down to the Membership Options section to customize it the way you want it. And don&#8217;t forget to click on the other tabs to configure the Permissions and Price Box as well.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-469907\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/create-a-membership-website-with-wordpress.jpg\" alt=\"create a membership website with wordpress\" width=\"562\" height=\"245\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/create-a-membership-website-with-wordpress.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/create-a-membership-website-with-wordpress-300x131.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, publish your membership level.</p>\n<p><strong>Step 4: Set Up Access Rules</strong></p>\n<p>You&#8217;ll want to make sure you define where and to who you want to restrict access on your membership website. So to do this, you need to set up rules.<br />\nGo to <strong>MemberPress » Rules</strong> in the left hand panel and select <strong>Add New</strong>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-469869\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/wordpress-membership-site-examples.jpg\" alt=\"wordpress membership site examples\" width=\"562\" height=\"254\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/wordpress-membership-site-examples.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/wordpress-membership-site-examples-300x136.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Now on the screen that appears, create a new rule to link your content to the membership levels you already created.</p>\n<p>For instance, you can select all the content under a specific category be accessible only by users with the 2 most expensive membership plans. In this example, we selected the <strong>Advanced WordPress Guide</strong> category.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-469870\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/wordpress-association-membership-plugin.jpg\" alt=\"wordpress association membership plugin\" width=\"562\" height=\"387\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/wordpress-association-membership-plugin.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/wordpress-association-membership-plugin-300x207.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Next head to the <strong>Drip/Expiration</strong> settings.</p>\n<p>If you choose to enable the <strong>Drip</strong> option, this will let you gradually release content.</p>\n<p>On the other hand, the <strong>Expiration</strong> option lets you choose the time when the content is no longer available.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-469900\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/drip-expiration-settings-memberpress-setup.jpg\" alt=\"drip expiration settings memberpress setup\" width=\"562\" height=\"186\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/drip-expiration-settings-memberpress-setup.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/drip-expiration-settings-memberpress-setup-300x99.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Once everything looks the way you want it to, save your rule. Now you can repeat this step to create more rules.</p>\n<p><strong>Step 5: Create Members Only Content</strong></p>\n<p>Next, you&#8217;ll want to create members only content so that you actually have premium content to offer people after they register for your membership site.</p>\n<p>You can add content with a post or page. So for this example, we&#8217;ll create content to link to the access rule we created in the last step.</p>\n<p>Create a new post and add the content you want to it. Next, select the <strong>Advanced WordPress Guide</strong> category.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-469871\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/creating-a-website-with-membership-and-user-login.jpg\" alt=\"creating a website with membership and user login\" width=\"562\" height=\"334\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/creating-a-website-with-membership-and-user-login.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/creating-a-website-with-membership-and-user-login-300x178.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, scroll down to the <strong>MemberPress Unauthorized Access</strong> section. Here you can set up what non-members (non-registered users) will see when they try to access this content.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-469878\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/membership-website-wordpress.jpg\" alt=\"membership website wordpress\" width=\"562\" height=\"327\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/membership-website-wordpress.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/membership-website-wordpress-300x175.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>And when everything is configured the way you&#8217;d like it, publish your page. Then, you can head to <strong>Posts » All Posts</strong> to see which content access is restricted to certain membership levels.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-469879\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/build-a-membership-premium-content.jpg\" alt=\"build a membership premium content\" width=\"562\" height=\"187\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/build-a-membership-premium-content.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/build-a-membership-premium-content-300x100.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p><strong>Step 6: Create a Pricing Page</strong></p>\n<p>In this next step, you&#8217;ll want to build a pricing page so your site visitors can see your different membership plans and sign up. MemberPress lets you do this easily from the Groups settings.</p>\n<p>Go to the left hand panel and select <strong>MemberPress » Groups</strong>. Next, click on the <strong>Add New</strong> button.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-469880\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/wordpress-membership-plugins.jpg\" alt=\"wordpress membership plugins\" width=\"562\" height=\"264\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/wordpress-membership-plugins.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/wordpress-membership-plugins-300x141.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Name your group something like &#8216;Pricing Plans&#8217; so people know what the page is about. After that, scroll down to the <strong>Group Options</strong> section. Here, you can add the memberships you want to show on your pricing page. You can also change the pricing page theme on this page.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-469883\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/membership-options-memberpress.jpg\" alt=\"membership options memberpress\" width=\"562\" height=\"409\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/membership-options-memberpress.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/membership-options-memberpress-300x218.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Now publish this page when you&#8217;re ready, and preview it to check it out.</p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s an example of how a pricing page will look on the default WordPress Twenty Nineteen theme:</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-469884\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/memberships-page-memberpress.jpg\" alt=\"memberships page memberpress\" width=\"562\" height=\"325\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/memberships-page-memberpress.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/memberships-page-memberpress-300x173.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Now to make sure your pricing page gets seen, you want to setup <a title=\"MemberPress\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/memberpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">MemberPress</a> to direct unregistered users to this page when they try and access members only content. In other words, when someone who hasn&#8217;t paid to access your premium content tries to, they&#8217;ll be sent to a sales page.</p>\n<p>To do this, go back to <strong>MemberPress » Groups</strong> and copy the URL of the group.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-469885\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/create-a-wordpress-membership.jpg\" alt=\"create a wordpress membership\" width=\"562\" height=\"186\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/create-a-wordpress-membership.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/create-a-wordpress-membership-300x99.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, head to <strong>MemberPress » Options</strong> and scroll down to the <strong>Unauthorized Access</strong> section. After that, check the box next to <strong>Redirect unauthorized visitors to a specific URL</strong> and paste the URL in the box below.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-469888\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/member-plugins-membership-content.jpg\" alt=\"member plugins membership content\" width=\"562\" height=\"322\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/member-plugins-membership-content.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/member-plugins-membership-content-300x172.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Finally, select the <strong>Update Options</strong> button to complete this step so unregistered users will be redirected.</p>\n<p><strong>Step 7: Add Sign Up and Login Forms</strong></p>\n<p>Now everything is almost all set up. So the final step is to add sign up and login forms to your membership site so people can access them.</p>\n<p>Let&#8217;s do this with a widget. Go to <strong>Appearance » Widgets</strong> from the left hand panel and drag the MemberPress login widget to a widget-ready area of your choice.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-469889\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/add-memberpress-to-wordpress-widget.jpg\" alt=\"add memberpress to wordpress widget\" width=\"562\" height=\"228\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/add-memberpress-to-wordpress-widget.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/add-memberpress-to-wordpress-widget-300x122.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, you&#8217;ll need to add your pricing page URL to the navigation menu so people can actually sign up.</p>\n<p>So head to <strong>Appearance » Menus</strong> and create a new menu or choose an existing one.</p>\n<p>After that, select <strong>Pricing Plans</strong> from the left under Groups and click on the <strong>Add to Menu</strong> button.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-469890\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/start-a-membership-site.jpg\" alt=\"start a membership site\" width=\"562\" height=\"455\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/start-a-membership-site.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/start-a-membership-site-300x243.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>And when your pricing page shows up below the <strong>Menu Structure</strong>, drag it to rearrange it to where you want it and then click Save.</p>\n<p>And that&#8217;s it! You&#8217;ve successfully created your Membership site with WordPress.</p>\n<h3>How to Get Analytics on Your Members</h3>\n<p>And now that you have a membership website, you&#8217;ll have a thriving and growing community that you&#8217;ll want to take good care of.</p>\n<p>Your next step is to optimize your membership site to get more traffic and more registrations. You can use <a href=\"http://www.monsterinsights.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">MonsterInsights</a> to take a look into the stats of your membership site.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-470364\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/membership-website-analytics-monsterinsights.jpg\" alt=\"membership website analytics monsterinsights\" width=\"562\" height=\"445\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/membership-website-analytics-monsterinsights.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/membership-website-analytics-monsterinsights-300x238.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>MonsterInsights is the best Google Analytics plugin for WordPress. You can use this plugin to get in-depth insights into what your registered users are doing, your transactions, and more.</p>\n<h3>How to Boost Your Site&#8217;s Membership Signups</h3>\n<p>Similarly, you&#8217;ll also want to focus on growing your membership signups on your site.</p>\n<p>You can use the <a href=\"http://optinmonster.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">OptinMonster</a> software to build your email list and let people know about your membership site. Check out this case study where <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/case-study-expat-com-grows-30000-members-month/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">one business uses OptinMonster to grow their online community by 30,000 members per month</a>!</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-470365\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/optinmonster-grow-membership-website-registrations.jpg\" alt=\"optinmonster grow membership website registrations\" width=\"562\" height=\"323\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/optinmonster-grow-membership-website-registrations.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/optinmonster-grow-membership-website-registrations-300x172.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>And there you have it. You now know how to create a membership site with WordPress using a membership plugin.</p>\n<p>Want to read about even more ways to boost your online income? Check out this article on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/wpforms-power-hacks-to-grow-your-business-online/\">WPForms power hacks to grow your business online.</a></p>\n<p>So what are you waiting for? Get started with the most powerful <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">WordPress forms plugin</a> today.</p>\n<p>If you like this article, then please follow us on <a href=\"http://facebook.com/wpforms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Facebook</a> and <a href=\"https://twitter.com/easywpforms?lang=en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Twitter</a> for more free WordPress tutorials.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/create-a-membership-site-with-wordpress/\">How to Create a Membership Site with WordPress (Easily)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:65:\"https://wpforms.com/create-a-membership-site-with-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:46:\"The 15 Greatest Natural Language Form Examples\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"https://wpforms.com/natural-language-form-examples/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"https://wpforms.com/natural-language-form-examples/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 15 May 2019 12:00:40 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Marketing\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"contact form\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:20:\"form conversion rate\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"aweber\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"lead generation\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"conversions\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"https://wpforms.com/?p=468117\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:569:\"<p>Want to see some cool Natural Language Form examples so you can start using it to increase your form conversion rates? Interactive forms are becoming popular really fast because it&#8217;s an effective way to get more website visitors to complete your forms. In this article, we&#8217;ve put together a list of some of the greatest [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/natural-language-form-examples/\">The 15 Greatest Natural Language Form Examples</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Lisa Gennaro\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18823:\"<p>Want to see some cool Natural Language Form examples so you can start using it to increase your form conversion rates? Interactive forms are becoming popular really fast because it&#8217;s an effective way to get more website visitors to complete your forms.</p>\n<p>In this article, we&#8217;ve put together a list of some of the greatest Natural Language Form examples for you to check out.</p>\n<h3>What Is A Natural Language Form?</h3>\n<p>A Natural Language Form is a type of web form that has text input form fields embedded inside of a conversationally styled sentence. This contemporary type of online form tends to be more engaging than traditional forms because of its narrative style. It&#8217;s more human, and people love that.</p>\n<p>Natural Language Form is also known as a &#8216;Mad Libs style form&#8217; by the UI community, based on the iconic US word game that has users insert their own word into a blank space inside of a pre-written sentence.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-469592\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/natural-language-form-examples-simple-form.jpg\" alt=\"natural language form examples simple form\" width=\"562\" height=\"176\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/natural-language-form-examples-simple-form.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/natural-language-form-examples-simple-form-300x94.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<h3>Natural Language Form Benefits</h3>\n<p>Conversational interfaces are said to be the next big thing in web forms and website visitor interaction. And for good reason.</p>\n<p>Here are some of the benefits of using Natural Language Form on your website:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Increased Conversion Rates.</strong> Conversational style forms can boost the success of your <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/lead-generation/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">lead generation</a> efforts.</li>\n<li><strong>Humanize Your Brand. </strong>Conversational marketing is a great way to let people know there are real humans behind your forms.</li>\n<li><strong>More Beautiful Design.</strong> The visual element of a form using conversational style is much more appealing to visitors.</li>\n<li><strong>Easy to Make. </strong>Modern form builders like <a href=\"http://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a> make it super simple to create forms with a drag and drop builder.</li>\n<li><strong>Ease of Use</strong>. These forms are easy to use and they have a superior user experience compared to traditional web forms.</li>\n<li><strong>Gather Better Data with Conditional Questions.</strong> You can adjust questions based on user&#8217;s answers to get more specific data right away by using <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/features/conditional-logic/\">conditional logic</a>.</li>\n<li><strong>Lower Abandonment Rates</strong>. Because <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/online-form-statistics-fact\">81% of people have abandoned a form</a> after starting to fill it out, form abandonment should be something every website owner focuses on.</li>\n<li><strong>Nurture Leads</strong>. More meaningful interaction helps your leads feel engaged and connected to your brand right away.</li>\n<li><strong>Increased User Attention.</strong> A simple form with targeted questions engages users as they interact.</li>\n<li><strong>Better Psychology.</strong> People love to talk about themselves and prefer to fill out forms they feel are talking with them, not at them.</li>\n<li><strong>Build Trust. </strong>Personalized questions make forms fields feel less mandatory and stiff, so people are more likely to trust them.</li>\n<li><strong>Connect With Your Users</strong>. Taking a conversational approach to your contact forms personalizes the experience for the visitor and starts nurturing the relationship right away so you can <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/insanely-easy-ways-to-grow-your-email-list-fast-starting-now/\">grow you email list fast</a>.</li>\n<li><strong>Modern Technology.</strong> Natural language form started showing up online around 2010 so it&#8217;s very new. Because of this, npl forms are popular on many sleek and professional-looking websites.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Natural Language Form Examples</h3>\n<p>Interactive forms with natural language and a gorgeous user interface are popping up all over the internet. And there are so many great ways to use them.</p>\n<p>Check out these great Natural Language Form Examples:</p>\n<p><strong>1.</strong> Kickstarter uses natural language forms to let users search for projects on their website.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-468277\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/natural-language-user-input-forms.jpg\" alt=\"natural language user input forms\" width=\"562\" height=\"644\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/natural-language-user-input-forms.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/natural-language-user-input-forms-262x300.jpg 262w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>2.</strong> The Conversational Forms Addon from WPForms uses interactive forms to engage visitors and improve the overall user experience, resulting in increased conversion rates. Check out this <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/conversational-forms-demo/\">conversational forms demo</a> to see it in action.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-456788\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/conversational-marketing-example-wpforms.gif\" alt=\"conversational-marketing-example-wpforms\" width=\"562\" height=\"405\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>3.</strong> Oscar qualifies leads automatically by asking users to put their zip codes into the form fields first. They use the input fields to make sure the website visitor lives in an area where they offer insurance coverage. And if they don&#8217;t, a message pops up and lets the website visitor know.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-468275\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/ui-pattern-form-fields.jpg\" alt=\"ui pattern form fields\" width=\"562\" height=\"318\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/ui-pattern-form-fields.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/ui-pattern-form-fields-300x170.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>4.</strong> This form suggests answers as well as lets the user enter their own into the form fields. This is a terrific way to put natural language form to work for you in your forms.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-468157\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/form-language-design-example.gif\" alt=\"form language design example\" width=\"562\" height=\"383\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>5.</strong> Although not a web form, in this case of natural language form, Domino&#8217;s offers a fun and quirky way to order pizza. They have interactive and automated text messaging that also uses natural language.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-456841\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/conversational-marketing-customer-experiences.jpg\" alt=\"conversational-marketing-customer-experiences\" width=\"562\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/conversational-marketing-customer-experiences.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/conversational-marketing-customer-experiences-300x160.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>6.</strong> Also, here&#8217;s another simple natural language form example for people looking for loans:</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-468312\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/web-form-field-labels.jpg\" alt=\"web form field labels\" width=\"562\" height=\"176\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/web-form-field-labels.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/web-form-field-labels-300x94.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>7.</strong> Codepunker has am interesting mix of natural language form and form language design with a single field for user input as well as dropdown field labels to limit the answers to a set of predetermined choices. In addition, they&#8217;ve also done a great job of customizing the submit button copy to seem more like a conversation is happening. Notice that it says &#8216;Where should I begin?&#8217; instead of something more generic like &#8216;Submit&#8217;.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-468311\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/natural-language-form-example-single-field.jpg\" alt=\"natural language form example single field\" width=\"562\" height=\"412\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/natural-language-form-example-single-field.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/natural-language-form-example-single-field-300x220.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>8.</strong> SuperCook has a simple form with straightforward use of natural language for their recipe search. It doesn&#8217;t use natural language form as heavily as some other examples, but it still gives us an idea of how simple some NLP forms can be.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-468317\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Natural-Language-Form-Examples-ui-pattern.jpg\" alt=\"Natural Language Form Examples ui pattern\" width=\"562\" height=\"252\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Natural-Language-Form-Examples-ui-pattern.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Natural-Language-Form-Examples-ui-pattern-300x135.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>9.</strong> Check out how Huffduffer uses natural language form in a clever way on their user registration form.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-468321\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/user-interface-contact-forms.jpg\" alt=\"user interface contact forms\" width=\"562\" height=\"481\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/user-interface-contact-forms.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/user-interface-contact-forms-300x257.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>10.</strong> This website organizes their interactive search results form according to conditional selections, meaning the output changes based on what the user selects.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-468322\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/user-experience-form-fields.jpg\" alt=\"user experience form fields\" width=\"562\" height=\"345\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/user-experience-form-fields.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/user-experience-form-fields-300x184.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>11.</strong> Also, it doesn&#8217;t always have to be about contact, registration or search forms. Check out this natural language form example that uses a popular TV character for a Mad Libs style form that&#8217;s just for fun.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-468323\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/mad-libs-style-form.jpg\" alt=\"mad libs style form\" width=\"562\" height=\"402\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/mad-libs-style-form.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/mad-libs-style-form-300x215.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>12.</strong> In this case this conversational style form uses interaction to get straight to the point and ask an important question about income level right away. In other words, forms like this help segment your leads so you can figure out which ones are higher quality.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-468333\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Natural-Language-Form-Examples-input-fields.jpg\" alt=\"Natural Language Form Examples input fields\" width=\"562\" height=\"252\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Natural-Language-Form-Examples-input-fields.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Natural-Language-Form-Examples-input-fields-300x135.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>13.</strong> Natural language form doesn&#8217;t have to be just for the front-end of a website. <a title=\"AWeber\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/aweber-2/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">AWeber</a> uses natural language form inside their product to help their customers build emails to send out. And they use a ton of different templates that offer this.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-468336\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/natural-language-form-simple-form.jpg\" alt=\"natural language form simple form\" width=\"562\" height=\"451\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/natural-language-form-simple-form.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/natural-language-form-simple-form-300x241.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>14</strong>. In addition, here&#8217;s a natural language form example being used within a Facebook chatbot. This is one of the many ways to use conversational marketing and natural language to engage customers and website visitors.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-457806\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/conversational-marketing-chatbot-example-messenger.jpg\" alt=\"conversational-marketing-chatbot-example-messenger\" width=\"562\" height=\"431\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/conversational-marketing-chatbot-example-messenger.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/conversational-marketing-chatbot-example-messenger-300x230.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>15.</strong> In this case we have another example of using dropdowns that only show pre-set answers as well as blank input fields. Using both is a smart way to take advantage of giving visitors freedom to put whatever they want inside the input fields. And this also helps guide them through filling out other input fields.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-468313\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/mad-libs-style-form-user-experience.jpg\" alt=\"mad libs style form user experience\" width=\"562\" height=\"485\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/mad-libs-style-form-user-experience.jpg 562w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/mad-libs-style-form-user-experience-300x259.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 562px) 100vw, 562px\" /></p>\n<h3>WPForms Conversational Forms</h3>\n<p>So now that you&#8217;ve seen some stunning natural language form examples, you&#8217;re probably curious how you can make some yourself! Well, because NPL forms act much like the process of an in-person, one-question-at-a-time conversation, Conversational Forms are a fantastic way to take advantage of many of their benefits.</p>\n<p>And it&#8217;s easy to get started with Natural Language Form and conversational interfaces.</p>\n<p>The simplest way is to use the WPForms <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/conversational-forms-addon/\">Conversational Forms Addon</a>.</p>\n<p>It offers a quick and easy setup of interactive forms. And if you&#8217;re already using WPForms, you can change your traditional web form to a conversational form in just a few little clicks.</p>\n<p>Plus, the best part is, it requires zero coding knowledge.</p>\n<p>In addition, you can use conversational forms to get increased conversion rates on:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong><a title=\"Surveys and Polls Addon\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/surveys-and-polls-addon/\">Survey Forms</a></strong> – Don&#8217;t overwhelm people with a lot of survey questions. Instead, use the Conversational Forms one-question-at-a-time approach to improve your survey completion rate.</li>\n<li><strong><a title=\"How to Create a Job Application Form in WordPress\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-create-a-job-application-form-in-wordpress/\">Job Application Form</a></strong> – Over half of the job seekers filling out your job application forms abandon them because they’re too long or complicated. With conversational forms, you can make your job application forms super simple.</li>\n<li><strong>Event Planning Form</strong> – As an event planner, you know how many questions you have to ask clients to plan the perfect event. The step by step approach helps you get the data you need without annoying your clients.</li>\n<li><strong><a title=\"User Registration Addon\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/user-registration-addon/\">User Registration Form</a></strong> – You can use conversational forms to improve your registration form conversation rate and build your <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/best-wordpress-membership-plugins-compared/\">membership site</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>So to get started, install <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/pricing/\">WPForms</a> and then check out our guide on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-create-a-simple-contact-form-in-wordpress/\">how to create a simple contact form in WordPress.</a></p>\n<p>After that, check out our step by step tutorial on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-install-and-use-the-conversational-forms-addon/\">how to install and use the Conversational Forms Addon</a> so you can get started using beautiful forms with an interactive interface right away.</p>\n<h3>In Conclusion</h3>\n<p>There you have it! You&#8217;ve now seen some of the greatest Natural Language Form examples and have a better idea how websites are using interactive forms to increase their conversion rates.</p>\n<p>If you want to learn even more about how interactive forms work, head over to our <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/ultimate-guide-to-conversational-marketing\">ultimate guide to conversational marketing</a>.</p>\n<p>What are you waiting for? Get started with the most powerful <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">WordPress forms plugin</a> today.</p>\n<p>If you like this article, then please follow us on <a href=\"http://facebook.com/wpforms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Facebook</a> and <a href=\"https://twitter.com/easywpforms?lang=en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Twitter</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/natural-language-form-examples/\">The 15 Greatest Natural Language Form Examples</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:56:\"https://wpforms.com/natural-language-form-examples/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:58:\"WPForms + Astra: Easily Build Beautiful WordPress Websites\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"https://wpforms.com/wpforms-astra-themes-easily-build-wordpress-websites/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:81:\"https://wpforms.com/wpforms-astra-themes-easily-build-wordpress-websites/#respond\";s:7:\"attrib